country
data.description: 2 letter country code so we can decide the search engine domain where to look for suggestions. A country code like `nl` for example will instruct the API to search on the dutch domain version of the search engine. Place `us` as the country code to search on .com

data.name: keyword
data.description: This is the keyword that will be queried for suggestions. This API does not use the adwords suggestions. It provides real search engine suggestions. You can submit multiple keywords here separated by a comma but keep in mind that you will be charged for each keyword with one unit.

data.name: language
data.description: A language code to be used when searching. Useful in google and youtube searching. For a full list of allowed languages please refer to our documentation.

data.name: source
data.description: Specify the source that you want to pull suggestions from. We currently support google, youtube and amazon.
